120
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:14,000
Çîmento kirin derê xerabe rind bûn. Ma we dît ev tiştên wisa
heta bi rengê gul çêkirin jê ra, ji me ra.
 
The bad roads were cemented and became good. You saw they
even made these things in the color of roses for them, for
us.

121
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:16,000
Û gundên jî, bi tuneyî me çêkiriye.
 
And the villages too, we built them entirely.

122
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:23,000
Me û serokê şaredariyê Hecer... û wî çaxê em ew bûn, em
meclîs bûn. Na wî çaxî qetî her kes cuda bû.
 
We and the mayor Hecer... and at that time we were that, we
were the council. No, at that time everyone was definitely
separate.

123
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:32,000
Wê çaxê me muwafaqe bir, her gundekî bi rêkê muxtêr, em
çîmentoyê û zirarê didin, û hûn jî rêkê xwe kûçe tê çêdikin.
Û me kir yanî.
 
At that time we got approval, for every village, through the
mukhtar, we give the cement and gravel, and you build your
own streets. And we did it, I mean.

124
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:38,000
Di vî hesabî... ku şeş gund man. Ji kokê çend gundan, şeş
gund man.
 
With this calculation... that six villages are left. Out of
all the villages, six villages are left.

125
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:41,000
Saet xwest. Noka em werin, em ser yaliya avê xeber bidin
hingî.
 
Health to you. Now let's come and talk about the water issue
then.

126
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:48,000
Çima ku tu dipirsî kîjan yaliya avê, em dibêjin ku dera
bajêrê Efrînê ye, ger gundewarên Efrînê ye, ger Efrîn bi xwe
ye, av kêm bûye.
 
Why, because if you ask which side about water, we say
whether it's the city of Afrin, or the countryside of Afrin,
or Afrin itself, water has decreased.

127
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:51,000
Em dixwazin werin bizanibin, ava Mabeta naha çawa ye?
 
We want to come and know, how is the water in Mabeta right
now?

128
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:55,000
Ava Mabeta naha sedî bîst û pênc tênê ne.
 
Mabeta's water right now is only twenty-five percent.

129
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,000
Ji bîra tên?
 
Is it coming from wells?

130
00:10:56,000 --> 00:11:04,000
Bîr yek e. Kanî yek e. Kanî jî di xwe da bîr hene. Ew du
qonax du mehete hene.
 
There is one well. One spring. The spring itself has wells
in it. There are two stations, two points.

131
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:10,000
Yek ê Dirêmiyê ye, navê xwe meşrûê Dirêmiyê de'm bîrê
Berbawîş. Kevn e ew.
 
One is Dirêmiyê, its name is Dirêmiyê project supporting the
Berbawîş well. That's old.

132
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:16,000
Wextê em derbas bûn meclîsa beledî kevin, me wî çaxê çêkir.
Ê bîrê Dirêmiyê.
 
When we entered the old municipal council, we built it then.
The well of Dirêmiyê.

133
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:21,000
Meşrûê avê Berbawîşê berî wî çêkiribûn. Rêviyê meşrûê
Berbawîşê av hişk bû.
 
The Berbawîş water project was built before that. The source
of the Berbawîş project dried up.

134
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:27,000
Wê çaxê ev xebitîn, heşt sal em ketin pê heta Dirêmiyê ji me
ra hazir kirin. Navê xwe de'm bîr Berbawîş.
 
At that time they worked, for eight years we pursued it
until they prepared Dirêmiyê for us. Its name is Berbawîş
support well.

135
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:32,000
Çima? Lewma li Berbawîşê mehettê avê tê wadanê heye, mudexe.
 
Why? Because in Berbawîş there is a water station, there is
pumping, a pump.

136
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:35,000
Ji wêrê tê, Mabeta û Qenterê, ev Mabeta û Qenterê.
 
It comes from there, Mabeta and Qenterê, this is Mabeta and
Qenterê.

137
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:42,000
Berî wê sê meh, millet bê av bû. Sebeba xwe çi bû? Av
dikişand. Îsal baran kêm e.
 
Three months before that, the people were without water.
What was the reason? The water was drawing back. This year
there's little rain.

138
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:46,000
Av dikişand heta çêkirin. Naha av tê. Bes av tê, têr nake.
 
The water was drawing back until they fixed it. Now water is
coming. But water comes, it's not enough.

139
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:50,000
Ji Mabeta... hezar û sêsed saet av e, gerek e.
 
For Mabeta... 1300 hours of water is needed.

140
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:56,000
Avêk din werin Mabeta û Qenterê, giring millet rehet avê
bixwe. Ger avêk din neyê, nabe.
 
Another water source needs to come to Mabeta and Qenterê,
it's important for people to comfortably use water. If
another water source doesn't come, it won't work.

141
00:11:56,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Dê em werin ser mijara bitenê, em gundekî gundekî dîn
neyêlikî.
 
Let's come to the topic alone, we won't talk about each and
every village.

142
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,000
Mabeta hefteyê çend rojan av tê wê derê?
 
How many days a week does water come to Mabeta?

143
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:05,000
Her deh rojan carek, deh rojan, dav donzdeh rojan av tê.
 
Once every ten days, ten days, even twelve days water comes.

144
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:08,000
Em werin alî çandiniyê. Çandiniya avê didin, av nadin, dar û
devî...
 
Let's come to agriculture. Do they give water for
agriculture, do they not give it, the trees and bushes...

145
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:18,000
Bi tevahî, millet avî nedî... ê gundê kaniyê av didî. Ê
gundê ne kaniyê... nikanin.
 
In general, people don't irrigate... The village with a
spring irrigates. The village without a spring... cannot.

146
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:27,000
Berê te dît salên bîst û çara bi baran bî. Bi baran kirin,
baran jî kêm bî. Û sala bîst û pênca baran nebarî û mûsim jî
tune ye.
 
In the past, you saw in the year 2024 it was rainy. They
relied on rain, and the rain was also scarce. And in the
year 2025, it didn't rain and there's no harvest either.

147
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:34,000
Gavê millet mecbûr bî dar... dar zer dibin û hişk dibin.
Lewma mecbûr bûn, çiqa bi yekî di şixulîn da...
 
Then the people were forced, trees... trees turn yellow and
dry up. Because they were forced, no matter how much it cost
them...

148
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:40,000
Cem vê derê me dûr û dorên me, hatin, heta çend bîran, yek
bîrê me heye.
 
Near here, around us, they came, up to several wells, we
have one well.

149
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:47,000
Di saetê de deh hezar, donzdeh hezar didin millet daku ev
zeytûnê av bidin digot ev darên zeytûnê hişk nebin. Çima?
Sebeb baran nebarî.
 
An hour for ten thousand, twelve thousand they give the
people so they can irrigate the olives, saying the olive
trees shouldn't dry out. Why? Because it didn't rain.

150
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:51,000
Em werin çi ye aliyê xwendinê, yanî ta'lîm. Niha çawa ye li
cem we?
 
Let's come to what is the aspect of education, I mean
teaching. How is it with you now?

151
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:59,000
Dibistan li cem me, derdorê sîh û yek sîh û du, mekteb li
nahiyeyê hene.
 
Schools here, there are around thirty-one, thirty-two
schools in the sub-district.

152
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:05,000
Jiyana xwendinê da maqbol e. Yanî mirov karê çi bike jê razî
be, rind e yanî.
 
In terms of education, it's acceptable. I mean, one sees
what work is done and is satisfied, it's good, I mean.

153
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:11,000
Çima? Mekteb jî vebûn, mamoste jî hatin, û dibistan jî
çêkirin û termîmê.
 
Why? Schools opened, teachers came, and schools were built
and restored.

154
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:17,000
Yanî çêkirinê pir dibistan helweşiyayî bûn, an yên xirabe
bûn, an yên ku hatibûn dizîn, termîm pir çêkirin.
 
I mean the building of many schools that were ruined, or the
ones that were bad, or the ones that had been robbed, they
did a lot of restoration.

155
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:27,000
Û saetên wan xwaş, wane çêkirin e. Geh heta dewletê hatiye,
ew munazemat hatin. Vê îşê yanî, jiyana xwendinê da rind bû.
 
And their hours are nice, they are doing lessons. At times
even the state has come, those organizations came. In this
work, I mean in the aspect of education, it was good.

156
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:35,000
Mesela wî çaxî em we dît her derê digeriyan, me di gundan va
we dît dersan didin. Me digot em giştika wern... êdî me kî.
 
For example, at that time you saw we were wandering
everywhere, we saw them giving lessons in the villages. We
said let's all come... then who are we.

157
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:44,000
Û rast e xelkî bi hev du re destê xwe da hevde û ev îşî...
yanî xwendin çîşekê pêşde ye. Ji ber hinek tiştên din gêr e
pir, pêşda ye.
 
And it's true, people joined hands together and this work...
I mean education is a little bit ahead. Compared to some
other things, it's very important, it's ahead.

158
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,000
Mamoste hene yanî li dibistanan te digot bêjin?
 
Are there teachers in the schools, as you were saying?

159
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:49,000
Hene... hene. Belê. Terbiyeyeke mezin e heye.
 
There are... there are. Yes. There is a great educational
system.

160
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:51,000
Spasiya te dikim, saetxweş.
 
I thank you, health to you.

161
00:13:51,000 --> 00:14:11,000
Serseriya min.
 
You're welcome.

162
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,000
Merheba xaltîkê min.
 
Hello, my aunt.

163
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:31,000
Berî giya saetî te xweş. Te xwarin me kir? Xaltîkê min em
werin... hûn bi mîvandariya me ne li gundê xwe, saetî te
xweş.
 
Welcome.

164
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:38,000
Berî giya saetî te xweş. Te xwarin me kir? Xaltîkê min em
werin... hûn bi mîvandariya me ne li gundê xwe, saetî te
xweş.
 
Before everything, health to you. Did you make us food? My
aunt, let's come... you are our guest in your village,
health to you.

165
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,000
Ehlen wa sehlen.
 
Welcome.

166
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,000
Em destpêkê te nas bikin. Navê te bi xêr?
 
Let's get to know you first. Your good name?

167
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,000
Navê min Cemîle ye.
 
My name is Cemile.

168
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,000
Bi xwe ji Mabeta ye?
 
Are you from Mabeta yourself?

169
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:48,000
Erê. Ez bi xwe ji Mabeta me. Navê min jî Cemîle ye.
 
Yes. I am from Mabeta myself. And my name is Cemile.

170
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:54,000
Dema em tên, em diherrin her gundekî, em dixwazin kesekî bi
temen mezin, bi emrêkî di mezin...
 
When we come, we go to every village, we want someone of an
older age, of a great age...

171
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:57,000
Em dixwazin em çîşkekî vegerin paş. Jê ma ra deng kin, ser
rojên berê.
 
We want to go back a little bit. Talk to us, about the days
of the past.

172
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:00,000
Em jî hênik nizanin, wek tu zanî em nizanin.
 
We also don't know some things, as you know, we don't know.

173
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,000
Yê te zanî.
 
Whatever you know.

174
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:08,000
Em dixwazin tu hinekî li ser wan rojên ji me ra deng bikî,
em kê werin ser jinên berê, jinên berê û yên niha em ê bînin
bîra te, tu ne ji jinên niha yî.
 
We want you to talk to us a bit about those days, let's come
to the women of the past, the women of the past and the ones
of today we'll remind you of, you're not from the women of
today.

175
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:15,000
Em tiştekî jinên niha nizanin. Jinên niha em nizanin, ew jî
me nizanin.
 
We don't know anything about the women of today. The women
of today we don't know, and they don't know us.

176
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:23,000
Em ê werin niha em ê pirs bikin berî giya. Çi cuda heye di
navbêna jinên berê û jinên niha de heye? Yanî çi ferq
mabênan de ye?
 
We'll come now, we'll ask before everything. What difference
is there between the women of the past and the women of
today? I mean, what difference is there between them?

177
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:32,000
Yarê min, jinên berê... îştê karê giran dikirin, şixulê
giran dikirin, şelek dikirin, kiftê xewra dikirin.
 
My dear, the women of the past... you see, they used to do
heavy work, they did heavy chores, they carried loads, they
made kufte and meals.

178
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:36,000
Jinên noka noka gî qolay e. Hazir didin destên wan tînin
dixwin. Ma êdî pir hazir dikine.
 
The women of today everything is easy. They bring it ready
and put it in their hands to eat. They prepare a lot of
ready things.

179
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:41,000
Û yên din nizanin jî, elemên wê tune, ser wan vîdeoyan, ji
xwe ra lê seyr dikin, çîva dikin.
 
And they don't even know other things, they have no
knowledge of it, they just watch themselves on those videos,
they browse.

180
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:51,000
Niha em bêjin wek tu xaltîkê berê, te hîn can bû, tu di
zemanê berê da... xaltîkê te çi dikir, te çi nedikir? Vê
destê te çi dikir û çi nedikir?
 
Now let's say like you, auntie, in the past, when you were
still young, in the old days... auntie, what did you do,
what didn't you do? What did this hand of yours do and what
did it not do?

181
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:59,000
Vê destê yarê min pale çinî ne, zeytûn çinî ne, dims
çêkiriye, mîj çêkirine... gişt çêkiriye zemanê berê re îştê.
 
This hand, my dear, has harvested crops, harvested olives,
made grape molasses, made raisins... has made everything for
the old days.

182
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:03,000
Naha tenê tu li mîna gundê Mabeta, te çêdikir an li xeynî te
jî jin hebûn?
 
Now, was it only you in a village like Mabeta who did this,
or were there other women besides you?

183
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:09,000
Çawa? Berê jinê êdî gî... wekî hev ji min meztir jî
çêdikirin... jin hebûn giya çêdikirin wekî me.
 
How so? In the past, all the women... alike, even those
older than me made it... there were women who all made it
like us.

184
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:11,000
Carekê te bûk xene kirin?
 
Did you ever put henna on a bride?

185
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:17,000
Erê me yek xene kir. Bas yek! Me gû ku xene kir.
 
Yes, we put henna on one. Just one! We put henna on a bride.

186
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,000
Xeneya berê çawa bû? Ku em li ser deng bikin.
 
How was the henna in the past? If we can talk about it.

187
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:26,000
Xeneya berê, îştê me xene bar dikir teştê. Yekê ji me ra av
germ dikir, lê dikir û me jî distira... distira.
 
The henna of the past, you see, we would load the henna in a
basin. Someone would heat water for us, pour it on, and we
would knead it... knead it.

188
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:33,000
Me dida hevala, û bûk rûniştin wekî te li cem min, bûkê
destê xwe nedida me, îlla gustîrkek zêr têxista pêçiyê
kirima nav.
 
We would give it to the friends, and the brides sat like you
next to me, the bride wouldn't give us her hand, unless we
put a gold ring on her finger.

189
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,000
Çi bûka?
 
Which bride?

190
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:38,000
Erê. Digot ma em mala şoşbên bin, berê şoşbe hebûn.
 
Yes. She would say, aren't we the family of the groomsmen,
in the past there were groomsmen.

191
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:41,000
Digot mala şoşpên kî, gustîrkê ke pêçiyê te?
 
Did she say whoever the groomsmen's family is, should put a
ring on your finger?

192
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:47,000
Me bûk xene kir, me gustîrkek kir pêçiyê. Hevalên wê jî em
wisa xene dikirin.
 
We put henna on the bride, we put a ring on her finger. We
also put henna on her friends like that.

193
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,000
Hevalên li Mabeta wê çaxê ew bûn?
 
Were those the friends in Mabeta at that time?

194
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:58,000
Erê li Mabeta. Kê bûk xene kira, digot mala şoşpêkê kî ye,
gustîrkekê wê de pêçiya kî... êvarê xene ye. Êvarî bûk xene
kir... ê ket pêçiyê kê... gustîrk.
 
Yes, in Mabeta. Whoever put henna on the bride, she would
say whose is the groomsmen's family, they should put a ring
on her finger... it's henna evening. In the evening they put
henna on the bride... and someone put a ring on her finger.

195
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,000
Û daweyên xwe... daweyên we çawa dikirin?
 
And your weddings... how did you do your weddings?

196
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:05,000
Dawet jî îştê, roj... roja... du roj, sê roj li defê
dixistin şêv ra.
 
Weddings as well, you see, a day... a day... two days, three
days they would beat the drum at night.

197
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:10,000
Û bûk, dima... berê li hespê dikirin. Hespê peyda dikirin.
 
And the bride, stayed... in the past they put her on a
horse. They found a horse.

198
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:15,000
Yekî serî dikşand yek jî du... yek jî bi kelekê diketin û
dibirin nav gund re digerandin, dibirin mal. Ev weha bû.
 
One pulled the head, one behind... one also walked
alongside, and they took her wandering through the village,
then took her home. It was like that.

199
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:18,000
Heta we giş derveyî gund bû?
 
Until you all went outside the village?

200
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:23,000
Li gund derve ba, bi mekîneyan dihanîn. Derêk dûr ba bi
mekîneyan dihanîn. Belê.
 
If she was outside the village, they brought her by car. If
it was a distant place, they brought her by car. Yes.

201
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:25,000
Çawa bû.
 
It was like that.

202
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:28,000
Xaltîka berê, jinên we dixwendin li Mabeta?
 
Auntie, in the past, did your women study in Mabeta?

203
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:34,000
Erê. Berê jin dixwendin, gundên me. Qîzek hebû, diçûn
dixwendin. Mekteb hebû.
 
Yes. In the past, women studied in our villages. If there
was a girl, they would go and study. There was a school.

204
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:41,000
Min go bavikê xwe ra, min go ez te dixwazim ez herim
bixwînim. Ê... digo heyte naşînim nav lawikan.
 
I said to my father, I said I want you to let me go study.
Yeah... he said I won't send you among boys.

205
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,000
Berê law û qîz tev hev bûn?
 
In the past, were boys and girls together?

206
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:53,000
Tev hev bûn. Digo ez te naşînim nav lawika. Digo tu qîzek î,
herî nav lawika, ez te naşînim nav lawika herî bixwînî. An
naşandim.
 
They were together. He said I will not send you among the
boys. He said you are a girl, you will go among boys, I will
not send you among boys to study. He didn't send me.

207
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:59,000
Aşqere. Diçûm piştî mektebê, diskinîm, min di şibakê re, li
qîzka seyr dikir... ez zehf ba tam mabûm.
 
Clear as day. I would go behind the school, stand, and watch
the girls through the window... I was very fascinated.

208
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:04,000
Min dida girî. Min digo dîka... min dico, eger, min digo her
bila.
 
I would start crying. I said... I said, well, I said
whatever.

209
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,000
Te çend salê bi te mêr kir xaltîk?
 
At what age did you marry, auntie?

210
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:11,000
Welleh deh û neh hebûn, deh û heşt bûn... Îştê wisa.
 
By God, there were nineteen, eighteen years old... That's
how it was.

211
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,000
Gava tu çûyî cihekî din...
 
When you went somewhere else...

212
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:14,000
Na! Çûcikek e.
 
No! She was a young bird (little girl).

213
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:21,000
Yanî, yanî em noka pirs dikin weke jinên berê bi mêr dibin
weha... deh û sê salî, deh û çar salî, diçûne.
 
I mean, I mean we now ask like the women of the past got
married like that... at thirteen, fourteen years old, they
would go.

214
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:25,000
Na. Jinên berê wisa nedikirin. Gişt kain, bîst salî... bîst
û du salî... bîst û sê salî, dikirin.
 
No. The women of the past didn't do that. They were all,
twenty years old... twenty-two years old... twenty-three
years old, when they did.

215
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,000
Jinê berê piçûk nedan. Noka piçûkan didinê.
 
They didn't give away young girls in the past. Now they give
away young ones.

216
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:30,000
Xaltîk ekê werim tiştekî wexta berê tu va hasidî bû bi kêf
bû wek te dît wexta we dît... tişt me nedidît... berê te
çûyî tu digiriyayî, te nexwest wekî bixwînî te dît wisa...
bi dilê te bû bibî tiştek?
 
Auntie, let me ask you something, in the past you were
jealous and fascinated when you saw... we didn't see it...
in the past you went and cried, you didn't want to just
study when you saw that... did you want to become something
in your heart?

217
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:35,000
Rind e. Noka ev a hesiyam e bi kor... kar tune kar ana... we
na çol e.
 
It's fine. Now I've felt it... I just sit blind... I can't
do any work... I'm sitting down.

218
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:44,000
Berê ez diçûm çolê, me kar dikir. Em dihatin me teştek nan
dikir. Me tiştkî xwe dikir... Me taştê dikir, me zeytûn
dikutan.
 
I used to go to the field. In the past I went to the field,
we did work. We would come and make a basin of bread. We
made breakfast, we crushed olives.

219
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:48,000
Me hêtûnc çêdikirin, em diçûn çolê jî wisa, terektor hişta
nebûn. Makîne îşta nebûn.
 
We made fig preserves, we went to the field like that too,
there were no tractors yet. There were no machines, you see.

220
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:58,000
Em bi meşê diçûn, û hîn me cewal jî bar dikir, karê... em bi
kelekê dihatin, heta me dihanî makbazekê... teqîn de
dihanîn... Bi darê li hev dixistin.
 
We went on foot, and we even loaded sacks, the work... we
walked alongside, until we brought it to the press... They
were bringing it with a blast... Beating it with a stick.

221
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:08,000
Em bi hal e, şev de çûyîn em giş sivê diçûn, me nane dikir
me karî dikir, em ka bi meşê diçûn, saeta ez dibêm saet e...
 
We were exhausted, we went at night, we all went in the
morning, we made bread, we did work, we walked on foot, the
hours I say are hours...

222
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,000
Saet e?
 
It takes hours?

223
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:14,000
Bi wexta diçûn karî saetan. Wê ro wê seetê jî seet bûn... em
wisa.
 
At the time they went to work for hours. That day that hour
was an hour... we were like that.

224
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:15,000
Xwedê canê te sax bike tê de.
 
May God give you health in it.

225
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:20,000
Tarîyê jî weha... sax be tu jî. Tarîya te jî weha ba, me
saeta xwe weha ba...
 
At night too like that... may you be healthy too. If your
time was like that, if our hours were like that...

226
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:22,000
Saetiya te xweş be xaltîkê min.
 
Health to you, my aunt.

227
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,000
Xwedê canê te xweş bike.
 
May God give you a good life.

228
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,000
Em te pir aciz dikin.
 
We are bothering you a lot.

229
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,000
Inşellah wextê te yî xweş be.
 
God willing, your times will be good.

230
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:28,000
Saetiya te xweş. Em gellek ji te razî ne xaltîkê min.
 
Health to you. We are very grateful to you, my aunt.

231
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:35,000
Em jî inşallah saetiya xwe xwaş dibînim. Inşallah xwedê
quweta te bide, em jî inşallah xêrekî rind bibînin, inşallah
wisa.
 
I also, God willing, see your time as good. God willing, may
God give you strength, and we too, God willing, will see a
good goodness, God willing, like that.

232
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:55,000
Saetiya te xweş xaltîkê.
 
Health to you, auntie.

233
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Xêr hatin Dîtin û Bêjin. Û di her xelekek Dîtin û Bêjin de
dîrok, bîranîn û tiştên gundekî...
 
Welcome to See and Tell. In every episode of See and Tell,
we discuss the history, memory and heritage of a village.

234
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:38,000
Û îro em hatine navçeyekê. Navçeya wek em dizanin dibêjin
ku, her navçeyek piştî ku gund ava bûne, navçe ava bûye.
 
And today we came to a district. A district that, as we
know, they say that every district was built after the
villages were built.

235
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:43,000
Werin em herin ji xalê xwe pirs bikin, ka ev tişt rast e lê
ne rast e.
 
Let's go and ask our uncle if this is true or not.

236
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,000
Merheba xalê min. Destpêkê em te nas bikin.
 
Hello my uncle. First let us get to know you.

237
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:48,000
Bi xêr hatin. Ser seran û ser çavan.
 
Welcome. You are very welcome.

238
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:54,000
Em dikarin pêşî navê te nas bikin?
 
Can we know your name first?

239
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:58,000
Navê min Mihemed Elî. Bavê Hozan.
 
My name is Mihemed Elî. Father of Hozan.

240
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,000
Şêrgelê Kurd e.
 
The Kurdish Lion.

241
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:02,000
Maaşallah.
 
Mashallah.

242
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:06,000
Û duyem xelat e...
 
And my second award...

243
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:09,000
Helbesta Kurdî...
 
Kurdish poetry...

244
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:13,000
Bi navê cîgerxwîn min wergirt.
 
I received it under the name of Cigerxwin.

245
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,000
Maaşallah.
 
Mashallah.

246
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:18,000
Tu bi xwe ji mabetayê yî?
 
Are you from Mabeta yourself?

247
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:20,000
Ez ji Mabetayê me.
 
I am from Mabeta.

248
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:25,000
Naha wekî dibêjin diyaloga ku me ya dirêj heye.
 
Now, as they say, we have a long dialogue.

249
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:31,000
Yanî maaşallah pir tişt li cem te hene, û ji miron tiştin ha
wilo di pişt kamerayê, naha em ê li ser kamerê jî deng
bikin.
 
I mean, mashallah, you have many things to share, and we
talked about many things behind the camera, now we will talk
about them on camera too.

250
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:35,000
Bes em dixwazin destpêkê, em werin dîroka Mabetayê.
 
But we want to first, let's come to the history of Mabeta.

251
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:39,000
Mabetayê berî gundan ava bû?
 
Was Mabeta built before the villages?

252
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:46,000
Em werin dîrokê bixwînin û lê vegerin...
 
Let's read the history and return to it...

253
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:50,000
Wek kal û bavê me ji me ra digotin...
 
As our grandfathers and fathers told us...

254
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:57,000
Teqrîben, ji heftsed û pêncî salî ve hatiye avakirin.
 
It was built approximately 750 years ago.

255
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,000
Heftsed û pêncî sal, belê.
 
750 years, yes.

256
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:02,000
Ê, gundên din... herêma Mabeta...
 
Uh, the other villages... the Mabeta region...

257
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:05,000
Giştik belkî kêmtir bûna.
 
Maybe all of them were less (younger).

258
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,000
Hmm.
 
Hmm.

259
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:08,000
Mabeta...
 
Mabeta...

260
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:10,000
Belkî ya ji bo çi?
 
Maybe for what?

261
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:17,000
Berê Mabeta, herêm bû mentîqe bû. Navê Efrîn tunebû.
 
In the past, Mabeta was a region, it was an area. Efrin
wasn't there.

262
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:20,000
Paşê Efrîn ava bû...
 
Later Efrin was built...

263
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:24,000
Mentîqe ji Mabetayê birin Efrînê.
 
They took the area administration from Mabeta to Efrin.

264
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:29,000
Mabeta... ji giyan kevntir e.
 
Mabeta... is older than all of them.

265
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

266
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:35,000
Lê belkî, gundin hebin...
 
But maybe, there are some villages...

267
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:40,000
Ji Mabetayê kevntir bin, bes pêş neketin wek Mabetayê.
 
That are older than Mabeta, but they didn't develop like
Mabeta.

268
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,000
Hmm.
 
Hmm.

269
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:47,000
Fa dimîne Mabeta, ew li pêş gundan e.
 
So Mabeta remains, it is ahead of the villages.

270
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:49,000
Berî gundan ava bû.
 
It was built before the villages.

271
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:54,000
Û çalakiyek aborî...
 
And an economic activity...

272
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,000
Ew tê da çêbû yanî.
 
That happened in it, you see.

273
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:59,000
Erê te da te pêşketin pir tê da çêbû.
 
Yes, much progress happened in it.

274
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:03,000
Naha em werin Mabeta, destpêkê ku ava bû wek ku hûn
radibêjin...
 
Now let's come to Mabeta, when it was first built as you
tell...

275
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:07,000
Xaniyên wê mezin bûn? Mesaha wê çiqas bû?
 
Were its houses big? How much was its area?

276
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:10,000
Sînorê wê gişkî ji ku heta kû bû?
 
Its borders... from where to where were its borders
entirely?

277
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:11,000
Sînorê wê...
 
Its borders...

278
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:14,000
Me go wextê ku...
 
We said the time when...

279
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:18,000
Berî fireh bibe û ava bibe...
 
Before it expanded and was built...

280
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:22,000
Ji ev meqfera heye...
 
From this outpost there is...

281
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

282
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:27,000
Ji meqferê û heta çarçiyê...
 
From the outpost and up to the square...

283
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:32,000
Û heta ha pê meclîsê bû ev.
 
And up to the council building, this was it.

284
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,000
Çi pêncsed malî yanî em bêjin.
 
So we could say like 500 houses.

285
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:37,000
Na, zêde e çarsed mal...
 
No, at most 400 houses...

286
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:42,000
Yanî îro tu li ser kaniyê kî rawestî, ji kaniyê diyar e...
ta jor diket jêr.
 
I mean today if you stand on the spring, it's clear from the
spring... up to the top and bottom.

287
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:44,000
Heta kolan hebûn.
 
Even there were streets.

288
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:46,000
Ziqeq hebûn, teng bûn.
 
There were alleys, they were narrow.

289
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:49,000
Ji wê xaniyê ta xaniyê serê te... didan hevdû..
 
From that house to the house above you... they connected...

290
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:55,000
Qunderî... ziqeqên wê teng bûn, ser xanî ra diçû.
 
It was muddy... its alleys were narrow, it went over the
house.

291
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:57,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

292
00:23:57,000 --> 00:24:01,000
Fa ev der, ew derên hanê... ewna Mabetayê kevn bûn.
 
So this place, those places... they were the old Mabeta.

293
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:03,000
Ha, Mabetayê kevn heye yanî...
 
Ah, so there is an old Mabeta...

294
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:08,000
Erê Mabetayê kevn heye, vêra dimînin yek sê mal kevn.
 
Yes, there is an old Mabeta, there remain one to three old
houses.

295
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:12,000
Yek mal ya... erdê Hacî Reş, şûnê firnê...
 
One is... Hacî Reş's land, the place of the bakery...

296
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:15,000
Hêrî Mehmû. Evna Mabetayê kevn in.
 
Hêrî Mehmû. These are the old Mabeta.

297
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:16,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

298
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:23,000
Hêrî Mehmû ha ew melab e, mektebek bû em diçûn topê
dilîstin.
 
Hêrî Mehmû, that is a stadium, there was a school and we
used to go play football.

299
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:25,000
Pêşî melab bû.
 
In the past it was a stadium.

300
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:26,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

301
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:31,000
Em werin naha malbatên ku hatine Mabeta ava kirine.
 
Let's come now to the families who came and built Mabeta.

302
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:35,000
Yanî hevna hatine vir, û hevna Mabeta ava kirin, em bêjin li
vir îstiqrar bûn.
 
I mean some came here, and some built Mabeta, let's say they
settled down here.

303
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:36,000
Û dû re aîle mezin bûn.
 
And then the families grew.

304
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:37,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

305
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:40,000
Pêşiyê kîjan hatine pêşî te zanî?
 
Which ones came first do you know?

306
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:41,000
Wela...
 
Well...

307
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:46,000
Tê gotin, li pir civatan hazir bûm.
 
It is said, I was present in many gatherings.

308
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:48,000
Diqutin.
 
They say.

309
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:53,000
Digotin e... teb û selef hat.
 
They said... ancestors came.

310
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:58,000
Navê wî Al bû, Al.
 
His name was Al, Al.

311
00:24:58,000 --> 00:25:00,000
Hewa ji kîderê hat?
 
Where did he come from?

312
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,000
Hewa ji...
 
He is from...

313
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:09,000
Ji gundê Tirkiyê, li ber Diyarbekirê helbestanê virna hatin
e.
 
From a village in Turkey, near Diyarbakir and Elbistan they
came here.

314
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:12,000
Wextê ew ji Tirkiyê hatin ne...
 
When they came from Turkey...

315
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:16,000
Wê hîngê, sînor tunebû.
 
At that time, there was no border.

316
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:19,000
Te sînor navbera me û Tirkiyê da tunebû.
 
There was no border between us and Turkey.

317
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:24,000
Koçer bûn, diçûn û dihatin...
 
They were nomads, they came and went...

318
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:27,000
Fa ji vir hatin.
 
So they came from here.

319
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:29,000
Bi pey ra, sînor hatin dîyarkirin.
 
Later, borders were set.

320
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:33,000
Hewa li vê derê man, em jî li vê derê man.
 
They stayed here, we stayed here too.

321
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:36,000
Fa ji berî giya Al hat.
 
So before anyone else Al came.

322
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:42,000
Diçû cîhek heye cem çayê, Miqarciqa ye navê wî.
 
He went to a place... there is a place near the river, its
name is Miqarciqa.

323
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:44,000
Li vir dirûnişt.
 
He settled down there.

324
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:46,000
Hewa li kîjan derê ve çiyayê? tiştek wilo ye?
 
Is that in which mountain? Something like that?

325
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:51,000
Ha ew li paş gund bi sê kîlometra ye.
 
It's behind the village by three kilometers.

326
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:56,000
Dibe li vir...
 
It happens here...

327
00:25:56,000 --> 00:26:05,000
Bazirganên ji vir dihatin da herin Ezkenderonê û dihatin
diçûn wira... diçûn Helebê.
 
The merchants from here were coming to go to Iskenderun and
they were coming and going there... going to Aleppo.

328
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:12,000
Dibe dihatin vir ra dibûn... digot ha li vir malbatek li vir
e, em li cem bisekinin.
 
When they came through here... they said oh there is a
family here, let's stop by them.

329
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:18,000
Diçûn rûdiniştin, av vedixwarin, nan dixwarin... vedihisîn.
 
They would go and sit, drink water, eat bread... rest.

330
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:21,000
Û lê diqesidîn diçûn Helebê.
 
And they would head out and go to Aleppo.

331
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:24,000
Di vegerê jî dîsa bi wî rengî, li cem vedihisîn.
 
On the return again the same way, they rested with them.

332
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:30,000
Nav derket, digot malbatek camêr li vir in em kêfxweşiya xwe
lê dibînin.
 
The name got out, they said there is a generous family here,
we find our joy in them.

333
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:33,000
Em herin cem wî rûnin.
 
Let's go sit with him.

334
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:36,000
Dû re Qerpûz hat.
 
Later Qerpûz came.

335
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:39,000
Qerpûz û Al.
 
Qerpûz and Al.

336
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:44,000
Qerpûz û Al destpêkê bingeha Mabetê ne.
 
Qerpûz and Al are initially the foundation of Mabeta.

337
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:49,000
Dû re yek heye Abûzer.
 
Then there is one Abûzer.

338
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:54,000
Abûzer, ew jî hat.
 
Abûzer, he also came.

339
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:57,000
Bi pey wan ra wisa malbat çêbûn.
 
After them, families were formed like this.

340
00:26:57,000 --> 00:27:02,000
Naha belkî yanzdeh malbat, di Mabetê da hene.
 
Now maybe eleven families exist in Mabeta.

341
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:06,000
Naha em bibêjin malbatên li vir çêbûn ji wan in?
 
Now let's say the families that formed in between, where did
they form, are they from them?

342
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:08,000
Yanî hew kok in ewên hatin?
 
I mean, are the ones who came the roots?

343
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:11,000
Ê hatine hev...
 
The ones who came...

344
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:15,000
Erê erê ez we nas dikim bes ez dibêm yanî malbatên ortê
çêbûn ji kîderê çêbûn?
 
Yes yes I know you but I am saying I mean the families that
formed in between where did they form?

345
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:22,000
Erê... hew tev zewicîn, mezin bûn, fireh bûn...
 
Yes... they all married, grew, expanded...

346
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:26,000
Belkî hinek hatin e, malbatin çûn e, hatin e.
 
Maybe some came, some families left, came.

347
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:29,000
Di pey re, dema ku hatin...
 
Later, when the nomads came...

348
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:34,000
Li gundan rûniştin, ew jî bûn malbat.
 
They settled in the villages, they also became families.

349
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:35,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

350
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:37,000
Naha...
 
Now...

351
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:41,000
Te got destpêkê, em bibêjin wek sêsed çarsed mal bûn.
 
You said in the beginning, let's say there were like 300 to
400 houses.

352
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:42,000
Naha wek em dibînin...
 
Now as we see...

353
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:45,000
Zêdetir î yêkî, pêtirî hezar û pêncsed male?
 
It's more than that, more than 1500 houses?

354
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:48,000
Hazar û dused û tiştek e.
 
1200 and something.

355
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:51,000
A hazar û dused. Belê. Naha mezin e.
 
Ah 1200. Yes. Now it's big.

356
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:57,000
Wê demê, em bêjin em kanin xwenek tiştkî li ser meîşetiya
diya denkin?
 
In that time, let's say, can we talk a little bit about the
living conditions?

357
00:27:57,000 --> 00:28:00,000
Bi çi awayî meîşeta xwe derbas dikirin?
 
How did they pass their livelihood?

358
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:04,000
Demê wê wextê... demê danokê...
 
In that time... the time of the harvest...

359
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:05,000
Wextê... ev pirs em divê bibêjin yani...
 
The time of... we must ask this...

360
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:07,000
Bi xwedê ez...
 
By God I...

361
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:11,000
Ez ji wê demê da tê me yanî...
 
I come from that time, you know...

362
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:21,000
Pir kêfxweşî hebû, rehetî hebû, hezkirin hebû, hevgirtin
hebû, çûyîn û hatin hebû...
 
There was a lot of joy, there was comfort, there was love,
there was solidarity, there was coming and going...

363
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:24,000
Yanî şevê... min...
 
I mean the night... I...

364
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:26,000
Şevekê em rûniştin e...
 
One night we sat down...

365
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:30,000
Bê sê çar mal tunebûn yanî.
 
There wasn't a night without 3-4 families.

366
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:38,000
Her malbatekê, çar pênc malbat dihatin cem hev.
 
To every family, four or five families came together.

367
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:45,000
Şevbêrka xwe derbas dikirin, bi çîrok û... bi kilam û...
 
They passed their evening gatherings, with stories and...
with songs and...

368
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:48,000
Tu bi çi dixwazî...
 
Whatever you want...

369
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:52,000
Ew kêf hebû yani, hezkirin hebû.
 
There was that joy you know, there was love.

370
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:56,000
Hevgirtinek hebû.
 
There was solidarity.

371
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:59,000
Tu dixwesti...
 
You wanted...

372
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:02,000
Ez tiştek ra mîsal kim wîna.
 
Let me give an example for something.

373
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:04,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

374
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:07,000
Di dewatan da... di cejnan da.
 
In weddings... in holidays.

375
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:08,000
Cejnê...
 
The holiday...

376
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:10,000
Ji serê gund.
 
From the top of the village.

377
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:12,000
Heta taliyê gund.
 
To the end of the village.

378
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:16,000
Qefle bi qefle dihatin.
 
They came group by group.

379
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:19,000
Pênc mêr, heft mêr, deh mêr.
 
Five men, seven men, ten men.

380
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:25,000
Serê gundê diketin, ha cejnê xwe dikirin heta taliyê.
 
They started at the top of the village, and celebrated their
holiday until the end.

381
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:29,000
Û yek tunebû li ser ewê digerî.
 
And there wasn't one who didn't visit it.

382
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:32,000
Di dewatan da... ew jî wilo.
 
In weddings... it was also like that.

383
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:34,000
Niha...
 
Now...

384
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:40,000
Belkî tu di navê gundekî da hefteyekê kes nebînî.
 
Maybe in a village you don't see anyone for a week.

385
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:41,000
Ne te dipirse...
 
No one asks about you...

386
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:46,000
Belkî... Pir caran di hundirê malê de dimirin kes nizanî.
 
Maybe... Many times you see they die inside the house and no
one knows.

387
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:48,000
Sê çar roj pê dihesin.
 
Three or four days later they find out.

388
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:49,000
Çima wilo bû?
 
Why did it become like that?

389
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:50,000
Yanî.
 
Meaning.

390
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:53,000
Zeman hov bûye...
 
The time has become harsh...

391
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:56,000
Rewş hov bûye...
 
The situation has become harsh...

392
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:58,000
Niha te qet behsa zeytûnan nekir.
 
Now you didn't talk about the olives at all.

393
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:00,000
Naka em dizanin gundiyê te dibêjin ku zeytûnên di herêma
Mabetayê de, em bibêjin, rengê wan cûda ye...
 
Now we know your villagers say that the olives in the Mabeta
region, let's say, their color is different...

394
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:04,000
Tiştekî wisa hatibû serê te yan na? Li Mabatoyê yan wî
wextî?
 
Did something like that happen to you or not? In Mabato or
at that time?

395
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:08,000
Na, hema wek Efrîniyan nedizanîn, giyayek e...
 
No, just like the people of Afrin didn't know, it's a
weed...

396
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:10,000
Giya bi erebî we nizanîbû yan çi?
 
You didn't know the word for weed in Arabic or what?

397
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:15,000
Zeytûn kêm bûn, li hember wê rez pir bûn.
 
Olives were scarce, but there were plenty of vineyards
instead.

398
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:23,000
Rez jî hebûn, lewma em diçûn, belkî dema rezan, bi mehan
xelk diçû ser ma'seran.
 
There were vineyards as well, so perhaps during the grape
harvest, people would go to the presses for months.

399
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:30,000
Dims çêdikirin, bastêq çêdikirin, sincix çêdikirin, tarsix
çêdikirin...
 
They would make grape molasses, fruit leather, walnut
sausages, and other grape products...

400
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:37,000
Bi mehan diman. Ked, doz, û fikrekî min dest pê kir.
 
They stayed for months. A labor, a struggle, and an idea of
mine began.

401
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:38,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

402
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:48,000
Di sala heştêyan da... min ev fikra, ku ez komake folklorî
çêkim... li Mabatoyê.
 
In the 1980s... I had this idea to create a folkloric
group... in Mabato.

403
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:49,000
Li Mabatoyê?
 
In Mabato?

404
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:54,000
Û li Efrînê wê hingê tu kom tune bûn.
 
And in Afrin at that time, there were no groups.

405
00:30:54,000 --> 00:31:11,000
Pir rexne hatin... min bi rkê xwe got ez ê çêkim.
 
A lot of criticism came... out of stubbornness, I said I
will make one.

406
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:23,000
Destpêkê em şeş kes bûn. Min dest pê kir, ez bûm û Ebû Ciwan
Ereb bû.
 
In the beginning, there were six of us. I started it, it was
me, and Ebû Ciwan who was an Arab.

407
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:31,000
Û Ehmed Osî bû, ew xortekî ji Amûdê ye.
 
And Ehmed Osî, that young man from Amûdê.

408
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:39,000
Û Rêber... Rêberê Armanc, niha me'rûf bi Rêber Armanc e.
 
And Rêber... Rêber of Armanc, now known as Rêber Armanc.

409
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:48,000
Û xortekî din hebû, rehmetî bû, Mihemed Elî ji Dirbêsiyê,
dixwend.
 
And there was another young man, he passed away, Mihemed Elî
from Dirbêsiyê, he was studying.

410
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:54,000
Û dû re çend kesên din hatin, Nezîr Palo...
 
And then a few others came, Nezîr Palo...

411
00:31:54,000 --> 00:32:04,000
Me istimrar kir heya sala heştê û sêyan. 1983'yan.
 
We continued until the year eighty-three. 1983.

412
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:11,000
Di 83'yan da... me xwest kom fireh bibe.
 
In '83... we wanted the group to expand.

413
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:21,000
Xortên din hatin, ciwanên din hatin...
 
Other young men came, other youths came...

414
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:29,000
Ez navê wan nakim, maneyek nexwe, welleh te navê min negot,
tu navê min ji bîr kirî.
 
I won't name them, lest someone gets upset, saying, "By God,
you didn't mention my name, you forgot my name."

415
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:42,000
Evê giya dikim, teqdîrî giya dikim. Elmuhim, di 83'yan da ez
çûm leşkeriyê.
 
I appreciate them all, I appreciate them all. Anyway, in '83
I went to the military.

416
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:51,000
Û dûrî min berdewam bûn. Kaseteke xwe ya yekê derxistin û
gihîştin rengekî ku niha wendayî ne.
 
And they continued without me. They released their first
cassette and reached a point where they are now lost.

417
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:57,000
Pirsek min heye. Min bîst, çi keçek ji koma hevalan da... ez
nizanim kîjan keçek e...
 
I have a question. I heard, a girl from the group of
friends... I don't know what girl it is...

418
00:32:57,000 --> 00:33:03,000
Dema ku we di wê pasê da bûn... û kaset we qeyd kir, ya koma
Armanc bû?
 
When you were in that bus... and you recorded the cassette,
was it the group Armanc?

419
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:06,000
Çi gotin ji te re hat gotin?
 
What words were said to you?

420
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:14,000
Hema berî ez çêkim, min ji milet re digot, em ê koma
qeşmeran çêkin.
 
Right before I formed it, I told the people, we will form a
group of clowns.

421
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:22,000
Digotin, çima em ê herin komê çêkin? Yek bireqise, bibin
qeşmer?
 
They were saying, why should we go and form a group? Someone
dances, to become clowns?

422
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:30,000
Elmuhim, pir, di rkê xwe de, me îla çêkir.
 
Anyway, a lot, out of stubbornness, we absolutely formed it.

423
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:36,000
Ez çûm leşkeriyê, ez da ketim silafê, îcaze hatim.
 
I went to the military, when I came down for greetings, I
came on leave.

424
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:43,000
Di Newrozê da... Newroza 84'an.
 
During Newroz... the Newroz of '84.

425
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:50,000
Em derketin, ez nizanibûm wan kasetek xwa derxistibûn.
 
We went out, I didn't know they had released their cassette.

426
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:55,000
Em li Eşrefiyê derketin pasê, em ê herin Newrozê.
 
We got on the bus in Eşrefiyê, we were going to Newroz.

427
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:59,000
Pas jî zihme ye. Ez li taliya pasê me.
 
The bus is crowded too. I am at the back of the bus.

428
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:08,000
Ew jî li pêşî ye, evê ku min jê re digotî te em kirin
qeşmer... Em nav nakin.
 
He was at the front, the one I told you said you made us
clowns... We won't name him.

429
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:10,000
Em bi nav nakin, belê.
 
We won't name him, yes.

430
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:15,000
Gava pas bi rê ket, kasetê Armanc a yekem, da ser.
 
When the bus started moving, he played the first Armanc
cassette.

431
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:21,000
Vêxist. Ez xerîbê welatê me. Pas qerebalix e, awiq bûye.
 
He turned it on. I am a stranger to our country. The bus is
full of people, it was packed.

432
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:30,000
Min dît ew ji serê pasê beziya cem min. Li taliya min, min
hembêz kir, maç kir û got, "Ebû Qurban, ez te bi me, ez, min
got te em kirin..."
 
I saw him run from the front of the bus to me. To the back
with me, he hugged me, kissed me and said, "Ebû Qurban, I
sacrifice for you, I, I said you made us..."

433
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:32,000
Yanî poşman bû?
 
So he regretted it?

434
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:37,000
Bes daxwezkî ez vê tiştî ji we re bibêjim yanî kurteyasî...
 
Just so I can tell you this thing, I mean briefly...

435
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:41,000
Mesele ku ev kesî nerazî bû ku ev kom çêbibe...
 
The story is that this person was against the formation of
this group...

436
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:54,000
Ji xalo re digot, "Hingê em ê bibin qeşmer"... xalo dema di
pasê de, heman kes, di destpêka pasê de bû, rûniştibû, û
çûkî da maç kir, piştî ku kaset pêxist.
 
He used to tell the uncle, "Then we'll become clowns"... the
uncle when in the bus, the same person, was at the front of
the bus, sitting, and went and kissed him, after he played
the cassette.

437
00:34:54,000 --> 00:35:01,000
Ev kurteyasî ye. Şuûra te wê demê çi bû? Dema te dît hat te
maç kir û derket. Wî ji te re çi gotin kir?
 
This is the summary. What did you feel at that time? When
you saw him come, kiss you and leave. What did he say to
you?

438
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:15,000
Min go, te ma negot te em kirin qeşmer? Go, te em kirin
qeşmer lê te em pêş xistin... wele wisa go, te em pêş
xistin. Û tiştek gelek baş bû...
 
I said, didn't you say you made us clowns? He said, you made
us clowns but you advanced us... by God he said so, you
advanced us. And it was a very good thing...

439
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:20,000
Û tiştekî me pêş diçû, hingê te tiştekî dîtir didît.
 
And something we were advancing, then you saw something
else.

440
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:25,000
Niha te ji min re tiştekî din jî got. Te got tu bi xwe
helbestvan î jî... helbestan dinivîsînî, pirtûkên te hene...
 
Now you told me something else too. You said you are a poet
yourself too... you write poems, you have books...

441
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:27,000
Dikarî bêjî jî?
 
Can you tell us?

442
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:32,000
Belê... dîwanên min hene, pênc çapkirî...
 
Yes... I have poetry books, five published...

443
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:39,000
Pirtûka çîrokan heye. Çîrok. Çapkirî ye.
 
There is a book of stories. Stories. It's published.

444
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:53,000
Û destnivîs: Pênc dîwan in... Sê misrehiyat in... şano... Du
roman in.
 
And manuscripts: There are five poetry books... Three
plays... theater... Two novels.

445
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:56,000
Navê wan çi ne? Romanên te...
 
What are their names? Your novels...

446
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:59,000
Dîwan, dîwan...
 
Poetry book, poetry book...

447
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:03,000
Ê derketine? Roman, ne rîwaye.
 
Have they been released? Novels, not stories.

448
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:14,000
Erê. Yek gundê Jînê ye. Û a din jî Ferhad û Nesrîn e.
 
Yes. One is the village of Jîn. And the other is Ferhad and
Nesrîn.

449
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:20,000
Te kengî dest bi vê karî kir? Nivîsandinê? Ger helbest e,
ger roman e, ger tiştek din.
 
When did you start this work? Writing? Whether it's a poem,
a novel, or something else.

450
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:23,000
Welehî min ji zaroktiya xwe da dest pê kir.
 
By God, I started from my childhood.

451
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:26,000
Xêr e...
 
Oh...

452
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:33,000
Ez hatim... ez ketim dibistanê. Gihîştim refa şeşan.
 
I came... I entered school. I reached the sixth grade.

453
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:40,000
Ez wekî erebî hewasek min jê re çêbû...
 
I developed a passion for Arabic...

454
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,000
Di nivîsandinê da?
 
In writing?

455
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:46,000
Na, di xwendinê da... hîn, hîn.
 
No, in reading... learning, learning.

456
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:54,000
Xêr e ez heme, ev alema giş heye. Zimanekî gişî ye em tunen
in.
 
What is this, I exist, this whole world exists. It's a
universal language but we are non-existent in it.

457
00:36:54,000 --> 00:37:00,000
Te nizanibû, ku bi zimanê Kurdî tu karî nivîsandin çêkî.
 
You didn't know that you could write in the Kurdish
language.

458
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:03,000
Zimanê nivîsandinê.
 
The written language.

459
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:13,000
Min rabû... tîpên erebî min dinivîsî bi Kurdî. Kurdî, tîpên
erebî min dinivîsî.
 
I got up... I wrote Kurdish with Arabic letters. Kurdish, I
wrote with Arabic letters.

460
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:19,000
Ez ketim refa heftan, min firansî xwend.
 
I entered the seventh grade, I studied French.

461
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:26,000
Firansî mi xwend... ez rojekî rastî... kovarekê hatim.
 
I studied French... one day I came across... a magazine.

462
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:31,000
Kovara Gulistan.
 
Gulistan magazine.

463
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:37,000
Zimanê min, mi firansî dixwend, min Gulistan xwend.
 
My language, I was reading French, I read Gulistan.

464
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:43,000
Dîtî ez zanim bixwînim. Nêzîkî hev e... tîpên firansî ye...
 
I saw that I know how to read it. They are close... it's
French letters...

465
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:49,000
Min adî xwend... Min go çi heye? Go ha bi Kurdî ye!
 
I read it normally... I said what is it? He said ah, it's in
Kurdish!

466
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:54,000
Tîpên Kurdî ne.
 
They are Kurdish letters.

467
00:37:54,000 --> 00:38:00,000
Ez ew bû. Ez vegeriyam ser tîpên Latînî.
 
That was me. I switched back to Latin letters.

468
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:08,000
Di sala 72'yan da...
 
In the year 1972...

469
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:18,000
Min helbestek çêkiribû. Destpêka wê hingê... ez bi keder û
kul bûm.
 
I had written a poem. Its beginning then... I was full of
sorrow and pain.

470
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:24,000
Mi go "Lo bira ez bi birîn im... Kul û derdan ez dikişînim."
 
I said, "Oh brother, I am wounded... I suffer from sorrow
and pain."

471
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:30,000
"Kul û derdên pir giran... Lê sa nekirin bav û kalan."
 
"Very heavy sorrow and pain... But the ancestors didn't heal
it."

472
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:33,000
Ev helbest dirêj e.
 
This poem is long.

473
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:38,000
Newrozek me çêkir... li bin kela Helebê...
 
We organized a Newroz... under the Citadel of Aleppo...

474
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:44,000
Bi dizî. Hindirekî wek vê, em heştê û sê kes tê de bûn.
 
Secretly. Inside a place like this, there were eighty-three
of us in it.

475
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:45,000
Di hewşa kelê?
 
In the courtyard of the citadel?

476
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:48,000
Bin kelê, jêr, erê.
 
Under the citadel, below, yes.

477
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:50,000
Yanî hewşek bû?
 
So it was a courtyard?

478
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:53,000
Hewşekî gird yê kelê ye.
 
It was a large courtyard of the citadel.

479
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:59,000
Em li wê hewşê da bûn... û da ko wek vê... Çima we li derve
çênekir?
 
We were in that courtyard... and down like this... Why
didn't you do it outside?

480
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:04,000
Em li Helebê bûn, li Helebê dixwend.
 
We were in Aleppo, studying in Aleppo.

481
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:09,000
Me li wê çêkir bi dizî... di hindir da.
 
We did it there secretly... inside.

482
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:14,000
Heştê û sê kes, vê helbestê min xwend.
 
Eighty-three people, I read this poem.

483
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:18,000
Ji heştê û sê kesan belkî bîst û pênc beziyîn...
 
Out of eighty-three people, maybe twenty-five ran away...

484
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:25,000
Min û ew reva kirin, "Ebo Qurban, te bi me, ev çiye? Tu ev
zemanê ji kû anî?"
 
He and I hugged, "Ebo Qurban, what did you do to us, what is
this? Where did you bring this era from?"

485
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:28,000
Hingê tunebû, qedexe bû...
 
At that time there was none, it was forbidden...

486
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:36,000
Bi dizî... malan da yekê tenê... kasetekê dapan ev, em ji
tirsan dimirin.
 
Secretly... in houses alone... putting on a cassette like
this, we were dying of fear.

487
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:39,000
Niha dema we behsa zimanê xwe dikir, tiştek anî bîra min.
 
Now when you were talking about your language, it reminded
me of something.

488
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:44,000
Em cilê ecêb in. Çûçik in. Gelekî min negehiştibû wan
wextan. Ez refê duduya bûm min dixwend.
 
We are a strange generation. We were children. I hadn't
reached those times much. I was in the second grade
studying.

489
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:47,000
Mamosteyek me Elewî hebû. Tê bîra min, carek tenê bû.
 
We had an Alevi teacher. I remember, it was just once.

490
00:39:47,000 --> 00:39:50,000
Min bi Kurdî deng kir, Kurdî Efrînkî.
 
I spoke in Kurdish, Afrin Kurdish.

491
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:56,000
Wê sê rojan ez fasil kirim, ji min re got, "Tu carek din
neyê vir û bi Kurdî deng bikî."
 
She suspended me for three days, told me, "You never come
here again and speak in Kurdish."

492
00:39:56,000 --> 00:40:00,000
Min wê çaxê fêhm nedikir. Yanî çima wisa dikin...
 
I didn't understand then. I mean, why would they do this...

493
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:02,000
Ta wê hingê ev meşhed we dîtibûn yan na?
 
Until that time, had you seen this scene or not?

494
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:04,000
Yanî em temenê me qe biçûk e, te bi xwe dîtîbû?
 
I mean, our age is quite young, had you seen it yourself?

495
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:06,000
Yanî qonaxek gelek hesas û mezin bû.
 
I mean, it was a very sensitive and major phase.

496
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:09,000
Haa... ê yek jê wek sirrekê ser re girt.
 
Haa... well, one would pass over it like a secret.

497
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:10,000
Çawa?
 
How?

498
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:12,000
Ê wisa te dîtibû û qet dihiştî ne tiştek e.
 
Like that, you saw it and completely acted like it was
nothing.

499
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:15,000
Ê çawa, kê îxrac qeyd derxist ji derve?
 
Well how, who got the ID extraction outside?

500
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:16,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

501
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:30,000
Yek ew bû l' Efrînê... yê sîcînê medenî, nabêjin Ebo
Mihemed, ê Ebo Ebo... ê nizam yekî kêş bû yekî... haşa haşa
yekî gemar bû.
 
One was in Afrin... the civilian prison's, don't they say
Ebo Mihemed, uh Ebo Ebo... I don't know he was forced
someone... God forbid, a filthy person.

502
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:37,000
Ez wileh... valî xo... hem... dused dane kurdî danîn kir.
 
I swear... his governor... also... placed two hundred in
Kurdish.

503
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:41,000
Mi dî go "Haş tehkû bi luxeti'l-cehş."
 
I saw he said "Don't speak in the donkey's language."

504
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:52,000
Ê em... em yanî zarok in em zaran in bes... ew jî... atîfî
qewmî ye di hundirê min de... germ e.
 
Well we... we I mean are kids we are kids but... that too...
is a nationalistic emotion inside me... it is warm.

505
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:54,000
Te re fiş nedibû wek çaxê naha?
 
You wouldn't get scared like nowadays?

506
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:59,000
Na. Mi go, xêr e lo... luxeta cehşan?
 
No. I said, what is it... donkey's language?

507
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:00,000
Hahaha.
 
Hahaha.

508
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:04,000
Mi go te ne... Xwedê ziman dayî... te jî?
 
I said haven't... God given a language... to you too?

509
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:09,000
Zimanê te te pê daxiviye... em jî zimanê xwe da xebitîn.
 
You speak your language... we also use our language.

510
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:14,000
Bi erebî yanî go "Teale bera, ma fî îxrac qeyd."
 
In Arabic I mean he said "Come outside, there is no ID
extraction."

511
00:41:14,000 --> 00:41:20,000
Em çûne wî îxrac qeydê me nedan min, çûm me bi kurdî
derxist.
 
We went to him he didn't give me our ID extraction, I went
and we got it out in Kurdish.

512
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:25,000
Wî ji ser wê da go... "Haş tehkû bi luxeti'l-cehş."
 
Because of that he said... "Don't speak in the donkey's
language."

513
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:27,000
Elhemdulîlah, elhemdulîlah am îro xilas bûn, ev şekil.
 
Thank God, thank God we are free today, from these types.

514
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:31,000
Elhemdulîlah. Xalo min... bi Xwedê min nedihişt ku...
hevpeyvîn xilas bibe.
 
Thank God. Uncle... I swear to God I didn't want... the
interview to end.

515
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:39,000
Yanî ez pir kêfxweş im, we me xweş dît, dem û deran dîtin
em... û ew demê te nas bikim, pir tiştan, spas ji we re,
demên we xweş.
 
I mean I am very happy, we found it pleasant, saw the times
and places we... and at that time I will know you, many
things, thank you, have a good time.

516
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:59,000
Spasiya te dikim.
 
I thank you.

517
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:40,000
Em her timî dibêjin ku jin di civaka me de rolekî xwe ya
mezin heye, û rolekî mezin dilîze.
 
We always say that women have a major role in our society,
and play a major role.

518
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:47,000
Wê lomê her û her e... ma te naha jî dît ku kesekî bi xwe
jinekê... gelek kar kiriye, gelek zordarî dîtiye.
 
Therefore always... well you saw now too that someone
herself a woman... has worked a lot, has seen a lot of
oppression.

519
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:52,000
Destpêkê, karê civakî dikir di meclisa mehelî ya Efrînê da.
 
Initially, she was doing social work in the local council of
Afrin.

520
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:58,000
Naha jî jina yekem e ku dibe... berpirsa belediyê.
 
And now she is the first woman who becomes... the head of
the municipality.

521
00:42:58,000 --> 00:43:00,000
Merheba mamoste Nazlî.
 
Hello Ms. Nazli.

522
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:01,000
Merheba ji te re.
 
Hello to you.

523
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:04,000
Maşallah wekî bi erebî dibêjin, xenîyetun eni't-te'rîf.
 
Mashallah as they say in Arabic, you need no introduction.

524
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:05,000
Spas ve.
 
Thank you.

525
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:11,000
Em dixwazin tu navê xwe û kîniya xwe kamil bêjî, ma ne ewê
te nas neke, bila te nas bike.
 
We want you to say your full name and surname, so if someone
doesn't know you, let them know you.

526
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:14,000
Navê min Nazlî Şêx Hesen e.
 
My name is Nazli Sheikh Hesen.

527
00:43:14,000 --> 00:43:19,000
Efrîniya... Mobeta me, tabîî navçeya Mobetayê.
 
Afrinian... I'm from Mabeta, a dependent of Mabeta district.

528
00:43:19,000 --> 00:43:28,000
Ji 2018an da em derketin... kelek ehlê xwe da me da Efrînê.
 
Since 2018 we went out... giving a lot of our people to
Afrin.

529
00:43:28,000 --> 00:43:31,000
Di navenda karûbarên civakî de min şixulî.
 
I worked in the social affairs center.

530
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:36,000
Heta 2024an, meha yanzdehan.
 
Until 2024, the eleventh month.

531
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:40,000
Berî Sûriyê ge... rizgar bibe.
 
Before Syria... got liberated.

532
00:43:40,000 --> 00:43:44,000
Mamoste Nazlî, wekî me pirs ser te bihîstiye...
 
Ms. Nazli, as we have heard questions about you...

533
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:49,000
Te gelek kar ji xelkê Efrînê re kir, te pir jinan ra alîkarî
kir.
 
You did a lot of work for the people of Afrin, you helped
many women.

534
00:43:49,000 --> 00:43:54,000
Yanî wek ku bi nêzîkî jinan ve te ta qedroya xwe kir, e cihê
te mezin e.
 
I mean as you were close to women, you acted up to your
position, your place is grand.

535
00:43:54,000 --> 00:43:57,000
Ez destpêkê dixwazim pîroz bikim, hev mensiba te ya nû ye.
 
First I want to congratulate you, on your new position.

536
00:43:57,000 --> 00:44:01,000
Û em dixwazin hinekî... tu ji me re bibêjî... çawa ev tişta
bû?
 
And we want a little bit... for you to tell us... how did
this happen?

537
00:44:01,000 --> 00:44:03,000
Çawa te ket vê derê?
 
How did you step into this place?

538
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:09,000
Û yanî çi karê te... e bêtir e te wekî dibêjin...
 
And I mean what work of yours... uh more as they say...

539
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:15,000
Sax bî... û înşallah jinên Efrînê giş pêş kevin.
 
Thank you... and hopefully all the women of Afrin will
progress.

540
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:25,000
Ez wek... ez jinek ji jinên Efrînê me. Pir jinên Efrînê,
kelek mêrxas derketin... kar dikin.
 
I am like... I am one of the women of Afrin. Many women of
Afrin, turned out to be very brave... they work.

541
00:44:25,000 --> 00:44:34,000
Me'rûf e, mintaqeta Efrînê ziraet e. Jinên Efrînê giştik
karê ziraetê dikin.
 
It's known, the Afrin region is agriculture. The women of
Afrin all do agricultural work.

542
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:45,000
2018an, me xwest ku em derkevin, jin jî basmek wê hebe, di
nav civakê de.
 
In 2018, we wanted to step out, for women to have their
imprint too, within the society.

543
00:44:45,000 --> 00:44:48,000
Yan bi bêjin di sewreyê de, xaseten yanî.
 
Or let's say in the revolution, especially I mean.

544
00:44:48,000 --> 00:44:59,000
Fe em derketin... kelek em li rex miletê xwe sekinîn. Kelek
însanên zeîf sekinîn, kelek jinan bi zatî xaseten em
sekinîn.
 
So we stepped out... we stood a lot by our people. We stood
by many weak people, many women essentially especially we
stood by.

545
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:03,000
Karê navenda karûbarên civakî pir xweş e.
 
The work of the social affairs center is very beautiful.

546
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:07,000
Ji dilve lê bêjim te re... pir çetin e.
 
To tell you from the bottom of the heart... it is very hard.

547
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:13,000
Tê de te di qiçkê ve fikirî, di jinan ve fikirî.
 
In it you thought about the child, you thought about the
women.

548
00:45:13,000 --> 00:45:18,000
Te pê hesî, ku ew zawiyeke hesas e.
 
You realized, that it is a sensitive aspect.

549
00:45:18,000 --> 00:45:30,000
Nefs el weqt tiştekî mezin e yanî, yanî tu rehet dibî,
welekîn piştî tu karê xwe dikî te pê hesî rehetbûnê ku kê ne
te bêtir dîtiye.
 
At the same time it is something big I mean, I mean you feel
relieved, however after doing your work you felt a relief
that no one saw more than you.

550
00:45:30,000 --> 00:45:35,000
Em dikarin bibêjin ku bandoreke te ya mezin liser civakê
heye û bi taybetî liser jinan.
 
We can say that you have a major impact on society, and
especially on women.

551
00:45:35,000 --> 00:45:41,000
Wê lomê wexta em dibêjin Mamoste Nazlî, ta vê gişk nas dikin
hûn kî ne, ev e Mamoste Nazlî.
 
Therefore when we say Ms. Nazli, to this end everyone knows
who you are, this is Ms. Nazli.

552
00:45:41,000 --> 00:45:42,000
Elhemdulelah.
 
Thank God.

553
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:48,000
Teb'en jinên me netîceyê herbê Sûriyê pir zulm dîtin.
 
Of course our women, as a result of the Syrian war, saw a
lot of oppression.

554
00:45:48,000 --> 00:46:01,000
Pir êş dîtin. Fe ji ber vê tiştî, înşallah, înşallah em
karibin welew cizek ji vê nahiyê de me derman kir.
 
They felt a lot of pain. So because of this, hopefully,
hopefully we managed even a fraction of this aspect, we
provided a remedy.

555
00:46:01,000 --> 00:46:08,000
Belê. Te karê xwe l'Efrînê kir, naha jî tu hatî Mobeta. Te
ket belediyê.
 
Yes. You did your work in Afrin, and now you have come to
Mabeta. You got into the municipality.

556
00:46:08,000 --> 00:46:18,000
Em dixwazin destpêkê zanibin, kes bi te re got xwe terşîh
bike yan a te bi xwe te xwest ku tu vê cihê bigrî, ji ber ku
tu hîn karê xwe berdewam bikî, karên ji vê mezin bikî?
 
We want to first know, did someone tell you to nominate
yourself or was it you yourself who wanted to take this
position, in order to continue your work, to do greater work
than this?

557
00:46:18,000 --> 00:46:30,000
Dîsa ez ê bêjim. Di navenda karûbarên civakî da, qeçkên sêwî
me neşatat ji wan re dikirin. Rihlat ji wan re dikirin.
 
Again I will say. In the social affairs center, for orphaned
children we used to do activities for them. We used to
organize trips for them.

558
00:46:30,000 --> 00:46:37,000
Rewşê xwe çetin em me'aşê jê re didîtin... yanî girêdanek di
navbera me de çêbû...
 
For difficult situations we used to find a salary for it...
I mean a connection was made between us...

559
00:46:37,000 --> 00:46:50,000
Jinên me meselen ê hene mêrê xwe dimirin, fe kar di dest de
tunebû. Fek em kelek alîkarî dikirin. Me meşarîe vedikirin,
me tedrîb dikirin.
 
Our women for example, there are those whose husbands die,
so there was no work available. So we helped a lot. We
opened projects, we gave training.

560
00:46:50,000 --> 00:47:07,000
Her yek meselen çi dixwestî, çi xwestekî vî çiye. Ê heye
meselen terzîtiyê dixwest. Ê heye meselen xelma wê terzîtiyê
ye. Ê heye meselen kuaferê dixwest. Ê heye meselen mûne.
 
Each one for example what they wanted, what is the desire
for this. There are some for example wanting tailoring.
There are some for example whose dream is tailoring. There
are some for example wanting to be a hairdresser. There are
some for example food preserving.

561
00:47:07,000 --> 00:47:11,000
Di mintaqeta Efrînê de pê meşhûr in yanî.
 
In the Afrin region they are famous for it, I mean.

562
00:47:11,000 --> 00:47:16,000
Xizmetên Mobeta pir dixwazî. Yanî di warê xizmetê, pir
dixwazî.
 
The services of Mabeta are needed a lot. I mean in the area
of service, it's very much needed.

563
00:47:16,000 --> 00:47:20,000
Heta niha cîhkî... pê naghîje Efrînê.
 
Until now... it doesn't reach Afrin.

564
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:21,000
Ji ber çi?
 
Because of what?

565
00:47:21,000 --> 00:47:25,000
Meselen em hatin vir... avê vexwarinê.
 
For example we came here... drinking water.

566
00:47:25,000 --> 00:47:30,000
16 mehete hene vir. 6 ji wan e şexal bin.
 
There are 16 stations here. 6 of them are operational.

567
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:35,000
Niha kar... elhemdulelah... dehan ji wan şixulîne, noka
halîyen.
 
Now the work... thank God... ten of them are working, now
currently.

568
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:41,000
Hîn 6 din mane. Teb'en ez hêvîdar im ne... hîn hewceyî wan
in şixulandinê ne inşeleh teala...
 
There are still 6 left. Of course I am hopeful that no...
they still need to be operated, God willing...

569
00:47:41,000 --> 00:47:42,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

570
00:47:42,000 --> 00:47:46,000
Ebsed tişt heqîqet qeçka tuneye li vir.
 
The simplest truth is there isn't a small park here.

571
00:47:46,000 --> 00:47:48,000
Yanî Mobetaya mezin û masahêt wî gelek fereh in.
 
I mean, a large Mabeta and its areas are very broad.

572
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:50,000
Çil û şeş gund in ha.
 
There are forty-six villages.

573
00:47:50,000 --> 00:47:51,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

574
00:47:51,000 --> 00:47:58,000
Merkezî Mobeta tenê nêzîkî dihezar aîla ye. Yanî 8-9 hezar
mirov tê de ye.
 
The center of Mabeta alone is close to two thousand
families. I mean 8-9 thousand people are in it.

575
00:47:58,000 --> 00:48:00,000
Fe hedîqet qeçka vir tuneye.
 
And there isn't even a small park here.

576
00:48:00,000 --> 00:48:01,000
Heta ebsed tiştî?
 
Even the simplest thing?

577
00:48:01,000 --> 00:48:06,000
Heta ebsed tişt e yanî. Û pir tişt... minelesef l' Mobeta
tuneye.
 
Even the simplest thing I mean. And many things...
unfortunately Mabeta doesn't have.

578
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:12,000
Yanî em karin bibêjin ku karê te li beledîyê da, key em
dikarin bibêjin... reîset beledîyê li vê derê.
 
So we can say that your work in the municipality, when can
we say... mayor of the municipality here.

579
00:48:12,000 --> 00:48:16,000
Te xizmetan ew tetwîr kir, çi ji miletî ra kir, te bi gî dî
de ye te?
 
You provided services and development, what did you do for
the people, what is in your vision?

580
00:48:16,000 --> 00:48:24,000
Dîsa em bêjin... em hatin meselen Mobeta riyê xwe jî pir
te'ban bûn. Ji mêj de çênebûne.
 
Again let's say... we came for example Mabeta's roads were
also very bad. They hadn't been fixed for a long time.

581
00:48:24,000 --> 00:48:38,000
Riyê gundan, riyê Efrînê bi şekil ahm. Mobeta em bi
mekaniyekî bi kirawa, riyek reîsî yê gunda... em wek
belediyê me hawar kir milet re.
 
The village roads, the Afrin roads in general. Mabeta we
with a rented vehicle, a main road of the village... we as
the municipality called out to the people.

582
00:48:38,000 --> 00:48:48,000
Me mevad teqdîm dikirin û se'yên milet hevrû dibûn, her
gundekî şebabên wî kom dibûn... fe riyek çêkirin bi vî
rengî...
 
We were providing materials and the efforts of the people
were combined, each village gathered their youth... so they
made a road in this way...

583
00:48:48,000 --> 00:48:49,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

584
00:48:49,000 --> 00:48:57,000
Dîsa zê bêjim, hîn pir riyek hene, tab'en teklufê xwe pir
in, seraha yanî.
 
Again I will say, there are still many roads, of course
their costs are high, honestly I mean.

585
00:48:57,000 --> 00:49:03,000
Belê ev jî delîlê gelek ewe delîlê ihtîmame. Yanî ihtîmamiya
te bi cihê te lê şuxule.
 
Yes this is also a sign of much care. I mean your care for
the place where you work.

586
00:49:03,000 --> 00:49:04,000
Elhemdulelah rabil alemîn.
 
All praise is due to the Lord of the worlds.

587
00:49:04,000 --> 00:49:09,000
Em ê axaftinê te caran bibîsin, înşelleh musteqbelen bi
xêr... ji mentiqeya Efrînê bi şekil ahm.
 
We will hear your words sometimes, hopefully in the future
with good... for the Afrin region in general.

588
00:49:09,000 --> 00:49:10,000
İnşallahû teala, inşallah ya reb.
 
God Almighty willing, God willing, oh Lord.

589
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:15,000
İnşallah. Spasiya te dikim, saeta te xweş, demên te gî xweş
inşallah.
 
God willing. I thank you, have a good time, may your times
all be good hopefully.

590
00:49:15,000 --> 00:49:35,000
Spas, wexta te jî xweş be inşallah.
 
Thank you, may your time be good too hopefully.

591
00:49:53,000 --> 00:49:57,000
Navçeya Mobeta. Li bakurê bajarê Efrînê dikeve.
 
Mabeta district. It is located to the north of the city of
Afrin.

592
00:49:57,000 --> 00:50:00,000
Herwiha dev û şeş kîlometreyan ji bajarê Efrînê dûr dikeve.
 
Also it is about sixteen kilometers away from the city of
Afrin.

593
00:50:00,000 --> 00:50:02,000
...û dor dikeve.
 
...and its surroundings.

594
00:50:02,000 --> 00:50:04,000
Hecmara malên vê navçeyê em kanin bibêjin,
 
We can say that the number of houses in this district,

595
00:50:04,000 --> 00:50:07,000
ji hezar û dusedî heya hezar û sêsed mal e.
 
is from 1,200 to 1,300.

596
00:50:07,000 --> 00:50:11,000
Herweha nêzî deh hezar û pêncsed heya deh hezar û şeşsed
kes,
 
Also, around 10,500 to 10,600 people,

597
00:50:11,000 --> 00:50:12,000
li vê derê dijîn.
 
live here.

598
00:50:12,000 --> 00:50:15,000
Û ez ê tiştekî din jî ji we re bibêjim,
 
And I will tell you something else too,

599
00:50:15,000 --> 00:50:18,000
di Efrînê bi giştî da, navçeya Mabeta,
 
in Afrin in general, the Mabeta district,

600
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:22,000
em kanin bibêjin ku weke dil, di ortê Efrînê da ye.
 
we can say that like a heart, it is in the middle of Afrin.

601
00:50:22,000 --> 00:50:24,000
Em dibêjin ne tenê bazara Efrînê,
 
We say not only the bazaar of Afrin,

602
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:27,000
hemû Efrîn û gundewarên wê...
 
but all of Afrin and its villages...

603
00:50:27,000 --> 00:50:32,000
[Music]
 
[Music]

